data.text:
LATROBE, PA—Over 600 hundred students were named to the Dean's List of Saint Vincent College for the fall 2023 semester, according to Dr. John Delaney, vice president for academic affairs and academic dean. In order to qualify for the Dean's List, a student must achieve a semester grade point average of 3.5 or better out of a possible 4.0.

The hometowns of members of the Dean’s List represented 24 states, including Pennsylvania, Arizona, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Florida, Georgia, Idaho, Illinois, Kentucky, Louisiana, Maryland, Massachusetts, Minnesota, Nevada, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New Mexico, New York, North Carolina, Ohio, Texas, Virginia and West Virginia and six foreign countries, including Argentina, Brazil, Germany, Senegal, Switzerland and Ukraine.

Students are listed according to their hometown residence. Each name is followed by the student's academic major.
